HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 401
BY REPRESENTATIVES BEAULLIEU, BRYANT, JACOB LANDRY, AND ST. BLANC
CONGRESS: Memorializes the United States Congress to work towards a cure for
Sanfilippo Syndrome
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To memorialize the United States Congress to work towards a cure for Sanfilippo
3 Syndrome.
4 WHEREAS, Sanfilippo syndrome, also known as "childhood Alzheimer's" or
5 "childhood dementia", is a rare group of inherited lysosomal storage disorders that mainly
6 affect a child's central nervous system; and
7 WHEREAS, Sanfilippo syndrome causes multiple cognitive, behavioral, and physical
8 symptoms that progressively get worse with time, with symptoms leading to premature
9 death; and
10 WHEREAS, this syndrome occurs when there is a deficiency in one of four enzymes
11 that affect the breakdown of heparan sulfate, a complex carbohydrate, leading to the buildup
12 in a child's cells, tissues, and organs, ultimately damaging them; and
13 WHEREAS, according to the Cure Sanfilippo Syndrome Foundation, the disease is
14 estimated to affect one in every seventy thousand births, and due to its rarity and mimicry
15 of other conditions, such as attention deficit/hyperactivity disorder (ADHD) or autism,
16 diagnosis is often delayed; and
17 WHEREAS, there are multiple treatments for symptom management to maintain
18 one's quality of life and prevent further complications, however, depending on the subtype,
19 the average life expectancy ranges from early teens to early thirties; and
20 WHEREAS, Shepard Guillory, son of Lafayette residents Natalie and Caleb Guillory,
21 brother of Ami Guillory, and grandson of Freddie and Janita DeCourt and Michelle Guillory
