1 and the late Scott Guillory, was born on January 23, 2025, and later diagnosed with
2 Sanfilippo syndrome on April 24, 2026; and
3 WHEREAS, scientific research and clinical trials are being conducted by multiple
4 institutions to further understand and develop a cure for the disease, there is still a need for
5 funding and general support for these projects; and
6 WHEREAS, families, like the Guillorys, facing the challenges of Sanfilippo
7 syndrome continue to advocate with urgent hope and resilience, looking toward a future
8 where breakthroughs will offer a cure for their children; and
9 WHEREAS, state legislatures have a long-standing role in urging federal action on
10 matters of national health importance and in advocating for policies that advance medical
11 research and public welfare.
12 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
13 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby memorialize the Congress of the United States to
14 prioritize research, clinical trials, and treatment development related to the cure of Sanfilippo
15 syndrome.
16 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the House of Representatives does hereby
17 extend its profoundest support, deepest encouragement, and most sincere wishes to Shepard
18 and the Guillory family as they face the daily challenges of Sanfilippo syndrome with
19 extraordinary grace, strength, and hope for a future cure.
20 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
21 presiding officers of the Senate and the House of Representatives of the Congress of the
22 United States of America, the Louisiana congressional delegation, and the parents of
23 Shepard Guillory, Natalie and Caleb Guillory.
